      "To move power efficiently over long distances, the generated electricity must be stepped up to one of these three specific transmission voltages."
    ],
    "questionText": "A technician is documenting a connection between a 'Nuclear' power station and the National Grid. To move this power efficiently over a long distance, it must be injected into the network at a transmission voltage. Identify the generation method used in this scenario and, from the following list, select the only voltage that is a valid UK transmission voltage: 11 kV, 33 kV, or 132 kV.",
